#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:115
msgid "PCIE PMU"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:117
msgid ""
"This PMU is located in the SOC fabric connecting the PCIE root complex (RC) "
"and the memory subsystem. It monitors all read/write traffic from the root "
"port(s) or a particular BDF in a PCIE RC to local or remote memory. There is "
"one PMU per PCIE RC in the SoC. Each RC can have up to 16 lanes that can be "
"bifurcated into up to 8 root ports. The traffic from each root port can be "
"filtered using RP or BDF filter. For example, specifying "
"\"src_rp_mask=0xFF\" means the PMU counter will capture traffic from all "
"RPs. Please see below for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:125
msgid ""
"The events and configuration options of this PMU device are described in "
"sysfs, see /sys/bus/event_source/devices/nvidia_pcie_pmu_<socket-"
"id>_rc_<pcie-rc-id>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:128
msgid ""
"The events in this PMU can be used to measure bandwidth, utilization, and "
"latency:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:131
msgid "rd_req: count the number of read requests by PCIE device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:132
msgid "wr_req: count the number of write requests by PCIE device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:133
#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:302
msgid "rd_bytes: count the number of bytes transferred by rd_req."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:134
#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:303
msgid "wr_bytes: count the number of bytes transferred by wr_req."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:135
msgid "rd_cum_outs: count outstanding rd_req each cycle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:136
#: ../../../admin-guide/perf/nvidia-tegra410-pmu.rst:304
msgid ""
"cycles: count the clock cycles of SOC fabric connected to the PCIE interface."
msgstr ""

